snippet.title: Hallmarks of Exceptional Quality Aluminium Extrusions
snippet.description:
Hallmarks of Exceptional Quality Aluminium Extrusions
Toegevoegd door Christialawrence laatste november
The demand of aluminium extrusions in various industries is high. However, not all vendors are experienced to provide great quality extrusions. 4 signs of a great extrusions are quality of raw material used, uniformity of metal thickness, adequate streamlining of junction points and smooth surface finish. More complex the cross section, more expertise is required to maintain the quality. One vendor that has the skill, the team, and the experience to provide high quality extrusions is P&A International. For more information log on to http://www.pa-international.com/products/diecasting-extrusions-china

snippet.title: How to polish aluminium profiles like a shining mirror
snippet.description:
How to polish aluminium profiles like a shining mirror
Toegevoegd door Wei Judy laatste juni
The acid brightening polishing,electrolytic polishing,polishing sliver anodizing,polishing electrophoresis, polishing nickeling. All of these surface need to be processed by mechanical polishing. Its purpose is to remove the natural oxide film and eliminate the extrusion scratching mark,aluminum profiles surface can be smooth and shining like a mirror. After processed by mechanical polishing with different kinds of chemical treatment, profile surface will have a bright,shinning. If it is equipped with aluminum profile coloration treatment, aluminum profile surface can be achieved various beautiful colors;it not only can be used at the simple architectural aluminum profiles, but also can process different kinds of complicated cross sectional profiles(flat, incline, arc face, tube, with grooves noodles) for furniture, bathroom, bags, home appliance, aluminium tile trim, wooden floor trim, stairs edge trim, door edge trim and other profiles.More details, welcome email: xixilyly@gmail.com

snippet.description:
Understanding Aluminium Die Casting
Toegevoegd door Christialawrence laatste december
Aluminium casts are lightweight & strong and therefore used extensively across industries. The process includes putting molten aluminium in alloy steel molds or die and then extracting it once it takes shape of the die. Specialized skills and expertise are required to get the work done. A leading producer of aluminium die casts is P&A International. To learn more Log on to http://www.pa-international.com.au/
